  <note>
    <title>Atrophic dermatofibroma</title>
    <created>20241206T020423Z</created>
    <updated>20241206T020444Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Atrophic dermatofibroma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The dermally located lesion is a poorly circumscribed proliferation of low cellularity, containing fibroblasts and some multinucleated cells in a collagenous background.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Basal epithelial proliferative lesion (see microscopic description)</title>
    <created>20170227T025808Z</created>
    <updated>20170227T025849Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows skin tissue with subepithelial proliferation of basaloid cells featuring  focal cellular atypism, occasional mitosis, and spindling pattern. Scattered melanin</div><div>pigmentations are seen within the tumor nests as well as in the superficial dermis. Connection between the lesional cells and the epidermis cannot be determined.</div><div>Retraction artifacts are focally seen around tumor nests. Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are negative for S-100, excluding melanocytic lesion. Total excision of</div><div>the tumor is recommended for a definitive diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Basosquamous cell carcinoma</title>
    <created>20250127T065540Z</created>
    <updated>20250127T065651Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Basosquamous cell carcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description: </div><div>Tumor histological type: Basosquamous cell carcinoma</div><div>Tumor grade: I (Well differentiated)</div><div>Tumor size: 1.2 cm in maximum dimension.</div><div>Tumor thickness: 0.4 cm.</div><div>Invasion depth: Invades the Dermis</div><div>Margins of excision:</div><div>  Peripheral margin: &lt;1 mm</div><div>  Deep margin: &lt;1 mm</div><div>Additional tumor features:</div><div>  Lymphovascular Invasion: Absent</div><div>  Perineural Invasion: Absent</div><div>  Necrosis: Absent</div><div>  Mitotic count / 5 hpf (mm2): 2</div><div>Lymph Node: not assessed.</div><div>pTNM: pT1.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>BCC (basal cell carcinoma)</title>
    <created>20161116T145034Z</created>
    <updated>20251029T032001Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Basal cell carcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a tumor (__ mm in maximum dimension) composed of lobules of basaloid cells bearing scant cytoplasm and featuring peripheral palisading, retraction artifact, and presence of scattered squamous eddies with dyskeratotic cells. Mucinous change of stroma is noted focally.</div><div><br/></div><div>Peripheral margin: </div><div>Deep margin: </div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div><div><a href="evernote:///view/26224745/s227/28e27278-fc64-bc84-7531-c91dde0dd3d9/e38a6072-a832-4f82-b2c0-624f58848a22">Basal cell carcinoma</a></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>BCC (suspect basosquamous carcinoma)</title>
    <created>20161117T134452Z</created>
    <updated>20250127T064557Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows lobules of basaloid cells bearing scant cytoplasm and featuring peripheral palisading, retraction artifact., and focal keratinization. In the deep portion of the tumor, there are infiltrative nests and cords of neoplastic cells that show more abundant cytoplasm with vesicular nuclei, which may represent squamous differentiation. The overall features suggest a basal cell carcinoma, in which a variant of basosquamous carcinoma cannot be excluded. Wide excision is recommended. The peripheral and deep margins are involved.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Blue nevus</title>
    <created>20170227T025218Z</created>
    <updated>20260512T044410Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Common blue nevus.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a picture of blue nevus with heavy melanin pigment deposition in the  dermal spindle cells which are intermingled with many melanophages. The epidermis is unremarkable. There is no evidence of malignancy.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Bowen disease</title>
    <created>20170731T075404Z</created>
    <updated>20170731T075415Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>It shows intraepithelial neoplastic growth of squamous epithelial cells devoid of</div><div>stromal invasion. Margins are not involved.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Bowen disease</title>
    <created>20170523T063729Z</created>
    <updated>20251124T060930Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="--en-fontfamily: sans-serif; font-family: Inter,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,sans-serif">Bowen disease</span></div><div><span style="--en-fontfamily: sans-serif; font-family: Inter,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="--en-fontfamily: sans-serif; font-family: Inter,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,sans-serif">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="--en-fontfamily: sans-serif; font-family: Inter,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,sans-serif">Sections show dysplastic squamous cells replacing the full epidermal layer. The margin is free with closest distance of _ mm from peripheral margin.</span></div><div><span style="--en-fontfamily: sans-serif; font-family: Inter,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="--en-fontfamily: sans-serif; font-family: Inter,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,sans-serif">(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</span></div><div><span style="--en-fontfamily: sans-serif; font-family: Inter,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><br/></div><div>[F] Malignant 213</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
