  <note>
    <title>Calcinosis cutis</title>
    <created>20170728T063103Z</created>
    <updated>20250226T023113Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>calcinosis cutis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;">Section shows skin tissue with dermal and subcutaneous deposition of numerous calcified materials. It may be a cutaneous phenomenon secondary to local tissue degeneration ("dystrophy") or may occur when the final metabolic defects give rise to elevated serum calcium or phosphate. Clinical correlation is suggested.    </span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180222T035845Z</created>
    <updated>20250221T025911Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">cherry angioma.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Section shows skin tissue with a small polypoid lesion consisting of multiple lobules of dilated and congested capillaries.</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20181205T013136Z</created>
    <updated>20201208T101641Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>chronic dermatitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue with perivascular lymphoplasmacytic infiltration in the su<span>    </span>perficial dermis. No maligancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20171228T042207Z</created>
    <updated>20250205T055902Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>http://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/skintumormelanocyticcompoundnevus.html</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Compound nevus.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows nevus cells in both junctional and intradermal areas, in which the cells mature with depth. <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Condyloma acuminatum</title>
    <created>20161213T004531Z</created>
    <updated>20250908T065201Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Condyloma acuminatum.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows the squamous epithelium displaying papillary proliferation in which the individual papillae are supported by a fibrovascular core and the hyperplastic squamous cells exhibit numerous koilocytes (perinuclear halo cells). No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20220415T023439Z</created>
    <updated>20220415T023829Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with accessory tragi.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a nodule covered by squamous epithelium with cutaneous adnexae and central cartilage.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20221026T034253Z</created>
    <updated>20221026T034451Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with follicular cyst, ruptured and inflamed.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue featuring marked mixed inflammatory cell infiltration that includes foreign body type multinucleated giant cells. There is identifiable residual hair shaft and squamous epithelium. The overall features are consistent with epidermal inclusion cyst, ruptured and inflamed.        </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180208T084506Z</created>
    <updated>20230607T025205Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">consistent with lentigo simplex.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Section shows skin tissue revealing epithelial basilar </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">hypermelanosis with slight elongation of rete ridges with </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">melanophages in the dermis.</span></div><div><span>    </span><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Consistent with ruptured epidermal inclusion cyst</title>
    <created>20171222T060142Z</created>
    <updated>20180313T052038Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';"><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Consistent with ruptured epidermal inclusion cyst</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows skin tissue exhibiting dermal infiltrate of mixed inflammatory cells, collections of histiocytes and aggregates of multinucleated giant cells. The features are compatible with a ruptured <span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">epidermal inclusion cyst.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Consistent with ruptured follicular cyst</title>
    <created>20161214T055251Z</created>
    <updated>20171214T054405Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows skin tissue exhibiting dermal infiltrate of mixed inflammatory cells, collections of histiocytes and aggregates of multinucleated giant cells. The features are compatible with a ruptured follicular cyst.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Corn (callus)</title>
    <created>20170728T062522Z</created>
    <updated>20251117T030227Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Corn (callus).</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The lesion is characterized by markedly thickened keratin layer and hyperplastic epithelium.    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Crush injury_C/W crush injury</title>
    <created>20170606T062038Z</created>
    <updated>20170606T062056Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows hemorrhage in the dermis and subcutaneous fat consistent with crushing  injury.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Cutaneous amyloidosiseous amyloidosis</title>
    <created>20180503T014604Z</created>
    <updated>20230920T060017Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows eosinophilic amorphous material deposition predominantly within subcutaneous layer and focally in the dermis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Congo red staining demonstrates apple-green birefringence under polarized light. Staining for PAS, desmin and S100 are negative. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Dermatofibroma [skiDF]</title>
    <created>20170118T080512Z</created>
    <updated>20260424T024451Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">dermatofibroma.</span></div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The dermally-located lesion is a poorly circumscribed proliferation of varying cellularity containing fibroblasts, histiocytes and mature collagen that exhibits a vague storiform pattern.</div><div><br/></div><div>Multinucleated giant cells with hemosiderin</div><div>pigment, as well as lipid-laden histiocytes are also</div><div>seen. Staining for CD34 is negative. No malignancy is</div><div>observed.        </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20190402T060053Z</created>
    <updated>20231108T033540Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Dermatofibroma with follicular induction in the overlying epidermis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>It shows a dermatofibroma in the dermis. The overlying epidermis is hyperplastic and acanthotic. Some of the rete</div><div>ridges of the hyperplastic epidermis is made up of basaloid cells. The peripheral row of these basaloid cells exhibits a palisading arrangement and is close contact with mesenchymal cells that reproduce a papillary mesenchymal body like structure of a primitive hair follicle. No evident cleft formation or increase mitoses, suggesting a basal cell</div><div>carcinoma, is present. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Dermatofibroma, cellular variant.</title>
    <created>20220531T051520Z</created>
    <updated>20241029T054328Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Dermatofibroma, cellular variant. See Note.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The dermal lesion shows proliferation of fibroblasts, histiocytes and mature collagen that exhibits a storiform pattern. There is increased cellularity and mitotic activity with central necrosis. Stainings for CD34 and AE1/AE3 are negative.  Lesional cells at the edge are positive for CD34.</div><div>The margin is &lt;1 mm from lesional cells. </div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: The risk of local recurrence is higher with this subtype.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>dermatofibroma, lipidized (&quot;Ankle Type&quot;) variant. [skiDF1]</title>
    <created>20180823T051610Z</created>
    <updated>20260424T024601Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>dermatofibroma, lipidized ("Ankle Type") variant.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The dermally-located lesion is a poorly circumscribed</div><div>proliferation of varying cellularity containing epithelioid to spindle cells, histiocytes and mature collagen. Some lesional cells show prominent nucleoli.</div><div>Multinucleated giant cells with hemosiderin</div><div>pigment, as well as numerous lipid-laden histiocytes are seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the lesional cells are negative for</div><div>SMA, AE1/AE3, S100 and Melan A. CD68 highlights the</div><div>histiocytes.</div><div><br/></div><div>The overall features are consistent with dermatofibroma of</div><div>lipidized ("Ankle Type") variant.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Dermatofibroma/Aneurysmal fibrous histiocytoma.  [skiDF]</title>
    <created>20170118T080512Z</created>
    <updated>20200401T015611Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Dermatofibroma, aneurysmal variant. See Note.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The dermally-located lesion is a poorly circumscribed proliferation of varying cellularity containing fibroblasts, histiocytes and mature collagen that exhibits a vague storiform pattern. There are large, irregular, blood-filled spaces and hemosiderin-laden macrophages</div><div><br/></div><div>Staining for CD34 is negative. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div>Note: The risk of local recurrence is higher with the aneurysmal subtype. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20200529T093723Z</created>
    <updated>20200529T093740Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Desmoplastic trichilemmoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows an epithelial tumor composed of clear cell with peripheral palisading nand focal presence of basement membrane. Focal area shows irregular epithelial nests and strands embedded in a desmoplastic stroma.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, the lesional cells are focally positive for CD34 and p16.</div><div>The overall features and consistent with desmoplastic trichilemmoma.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20181210T054035Z</created>
    <updated>20230710T024908Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>dilated pore.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a keratin-plugged cystically dilated follicle which is superficially located. It is lined by stratified squamous epithelium which is acanthotic with irregular budding.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Dysplastic nevus.</title>
    <created>20251208T014919Z</created>
    <updated>20251208T014945Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The section reveals junctional and dermal melanocytes arranged in irregular nests and as single units. Bridging of the rete ridges is also present. Lamellar fibroplasia and a scattered lymphocytic infiltrate are noted in the dermis. The surgical margin is free of the lesion, with the closest distance measuring 1 mm. Clinical follow-up is recommended.</div><div><br/></div><div>Ancillary studies: </div><div>HMB45: Focally positive with superficial staining. </div><div>P16: Positive</div><div>Ki67: 1%</div><div>BRAF(VE1): Positive.</div><div>BAP1: Positive.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Eccrine poroma</title>
    <created>20161228T060404Z</created>
    <updated>20230616T032743Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>eccrine poroma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows broad anastomosing bands of uniformly small cuboidal cells connected intercellular bridges. Narrow ductal lumen is also seen noted within the tumor bands.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Eccrine spiradenoma</title>
    <created>20170728T062702Z</created>
    <updated>20240318T032753Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>eccrine spiradenoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The tumor consists of a couple of sharply demarcated lobules within the dermis that show no connections with the epidermis.</div><div>The lobules are made up of two types of epithelial cells arranged in intertwining cords. Cells with small, dark nuclei lie at the periphery of the bands and cells with large pale nuclei that lie in the center of the bands and around small lumina. The lumina</div><div>frequently contain small amounts of eosinophilic material.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Epidermal nevus.</title>
    <created>20180131T044637Z</created>
    <updated>20230713T081350Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Epidermal nevus.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Section shows acanthosis and papillomatosis of squamous epithelium, accompanied by chronic inflammation in the dermis.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Epidermoid cyst, keratin substance only [SKI15K]</title>
    <created>20171211T082204Z</created>
    <updated>20250219T033638Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Epidermoid cyst,<span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 9pt;"> keratin substance only</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 9pt;">Microscopic description:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Section shows laminated keratin fragments only.    </span></span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Erythema nodosum</title>
    <created>20170323T075318Z</created>
    <updated>20231102T080209Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The histologic section is mainly confined to the subcutaneous tissue which shows</div><div>septal inflammation spread into the adjacent lobule. In addition, there are</div><div>conspicuous granulomata composed of histiocytes with multinucleated giant cells, and</div><div>occasional eosinophils and neutrophils. Miescher radial granuloma characterized by</div><div>aggregations of small histiocytes around a central clef is also seen.</div><div>Perivascular lymphocytic infiltrate is seen at deep dermis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Special stainings (acid fast, Auramine-Rhodamine, GMS and PAS) show no micro-organism</div><div>in the granulomas. No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>FB retention</title>
    <created>20180709T032745Z</created>
    <updated>20230629T032612Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Consistent with foreign body retention</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue with epidermial defect and chronic inflammatory infiltrate in the dermis. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>FB retention 1C [FB}</title>
    <created>20191022T052026Z</created>
    <updated>20230526T021722Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>_____, removal of foreign body --- Consistent with foreign body retention.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of one piece of foreign body material measuring _ cm in size.</div><div>[gross examination only]</div><div><span>    </span><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>fibrosarcomatous dermatofibrosarcoma DFSP</title>
    <created>20211027T070216Z</created>
    <updated>20240927T050601Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>fibrosarcomatous dermatofibrosarcoma</div><div><span>    </span><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Tumor type: fibrosarcomatous dermatofibrosarcoma</div><div>  protuberans.</div><div>Tumor size: __ cm at greatest dimension</div><div>Tumor location: chest wall, within dermis and subcutis</div><div>Surgical margin: free of tumor, with closest distance of 1</div><div>  cm from peripheral margin</div><div>FNCLCC grading: grade 1</div><div>- Differentiation: score 1</div><div>- Mitotic count: score 2, 15/10HPF</div><div>- Tumor necrosis: score 0, no necrosis</div><div>pTNM: pTlNx.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>focal mucinosis.</title>
    <created>20210330T060622Z</created>
    <updated>20210330T060629Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>focal mucinosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows interstitial mucin deposits in widened spaces</div><div>between collagen bundles in the dermis, admixed with bland</div><div>fibroblastic cells being focally positive for CD34 but not</div><div>S100, EMA, SMA, desmin or ER. The mucin is positive for</div><div>mucicarmine but not PAS. The overall features are most</div><div>consistent with focal mucinosis.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Follicular cyst [SKI12]</title>
    <created>20220421T061600Z</created>
    <updated>20230830T070446Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>follicular cyst.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The cyst is lined by stratified squamous epithelium connecting to the overlying skin. Its lumen contains keratin material. No evidence of inflammation or malignancy is noted.</div><div>    </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Follicular cyst [SKI12FB]</title>
    <created>20170728T062623Z</created>
    <updated>20230713T030948Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">follicular cyst, inflamed.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The cyst is lined by stratified squamous epithelium connecting to the overlying skin, <span style="line-height: 1.45;">associated with a foreign body granulomatous response. </span>Its lumen contains keratin material. No evidence of malignancy is noted.<span>    </span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Follicular cyst, inflamed [Ski12in]</title>
    <created>20170728T062642Z</created>
    <updated>20230606T081019Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">follicular cyst, inflamed.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The cyst is lined by stratified squamous epithelium connecting to the overlying skin. Its lumen contains keratin material. Inflammatory reaction is present. No evidence of malignancy is noted.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Follicular cyst, ruptured and inflamed. [SKI12A]</title>
    <created>20180301T033258Z</created>
    <updated>20231108T033437Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">follicular cyst, ruptured and inflamed.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">The cyst is lined by stratified squamous epithelium connecting to the overlying skin. At its epithelial-stromal interface, there is marked mixed inflammatory cell infiltration that includes foreign body type multinucleated giant cells. The lumen is partially obliterated by deposition of similar type of inflammatory cells, with identifiable residual keratin material.        </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Folliculitis</title>
    <created>20170227T030342Z</created>
    <updated>20170227T030353Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The skin tissue shows mild acanthosis of epidermis with elongated rete ridges. Infiltrate of neutrophils and lymphocytes are seen within follicular epithelium.</div><div>Associated granulomatous reaction is seen in the adjacent dermis. Perivascular infiltrate of chronic inflammatory cells are seen. No fungus is demonstrated by GMS and PAS.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Folliculosebaceous cystic hamartoma.</title>
    <created>20180323T075437Z</created>
    <updated>20200618T045454Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>folliculosebaceous cystic hamartoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows hair follicles with sebaceous differentiation in a fibrous stroma.</div><div><br/></div><div>folliculosebaceous cystic hamartoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a dermal-based lesion composed of cystic cavities with secretions in the lumen, accompanied by hair follicles, sebaceous glands, in a stroma containing fibrous and adipose tissue.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>foreign body granuloma [silicone]</title>
    <created>20190501T013149Z</created>
    <updated>20251028T063115Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Foreign body granuloma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows variable-sized spaces surrounded by histiocytes, resembling lipoblasts. The histiocytes are positive for CD68 but not S100 or CDK4. Foreign body such as silicone should be considered. Please correlate clinically.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Gangrene</title>
    <created>20180207T075730Z</created>
    <updated>20250402T025226Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Gangrene</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Sections of the skin and soft tissue show liquefactive necrosis with heavy PMN infiltrate as well as lymphoplasmacytic cells infiltrate.</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Granulation tissue with chronic active inflammation.</title>
    <created>20180323T061418Z</created>
    <updated>20181011T062752Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Granulation tissue with chronic active inflammation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows dermal and subcutaneous tissue featuring granulation tissue with infiltrate of acute and chronic inflammatory cells admixed with histiocytes and occasional multinucleated giant cells.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Haluronic acid fillers</title>
    <created>20170221T092603Z</created>
    <updated>20170221T092627Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows pools of basophilic amorphous substances within soft tissue with surrounding granulomatous reaction. These deposits are positive for alcian blue</div><div>stain. The findings may suggest hyaluronic acid fillers. Clinical correlation is recommended.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Hidradenitis suppurativa</title>
    <created>20170120T052541Z</created>
    <updated>20170120T052558Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>

<div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><br/><div>Consistent with hidradenitis suppurativa, _ axilla, excision</div></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><div><br/></div></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Section shows epithelial-lined sinus tracts with mixed inflammation and granulation tissue as well as multinucleated giant cells in the underlying stroma, consistent with hidradenitis suppurativa. No malignancy is observed.</div></div><div><br/>

</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180626T042505Z</created>
    <updated>20250305T024102Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Hidradenoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a dermal-located lesion with solid and cystic growth. It is comosed of clear or pale cells admixed with squamoid cells in a fibrovascular and hyalinized stroma.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20190626T053448Z</created>
    <updated>20260422T045228Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Hidrocystoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue with a dermally-located cystic lesion lined by inner columnar</div><div>cells and outer myoepithelial cells. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Hyperpigmentation</title>
    <created>20180208T084506Z</created>
    <updated>20230607T031222Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>excisional biopsy --- hyperpigmentation.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Section shows skin tissue revealing epithelial </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">basilar </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">hypermelanosis.</span></div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Hypertrophic scar</title>
    <created>20171211T081954Z</created>
    <updated>20230711T031040Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">hypertrophic scar.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Dense and hypertrophic collagenous fibers with <span style="line-height: 1.45;">perpendicular running vessels are seen in the dermis. Focal hemorrhage and chronic inflammatory infiltrate are also noted. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div>    </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>IDN Intradermal nevus</title>
    <created>20170217T061604Z</created>
    <updated>20231227T060539Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 16px;">intradermal nevus.</span></div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 16px;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 16px;">It shows intact epidermis with intradermal lobules or nests of mature nevus cells. No junctional activity is noted. No malignancy is observed.                </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>IDN+SKI15</title>
    <created>20211001T045132Z</created>
    <updated>20251117T030007Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>-- Intradermal nevus.</div><div>-- Epidermoid cyst.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>It shows intact epidermis with intradermal lobules or nests of mature nevus cells. No junctional activity is noted.</div><div>There is also a dermally-located cyst lined by squamous epithelium with keratin fragments in its lumen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>inverted follicular keratosisinverted follicular keratosis</title>
    <created>20181109T113827Z</created>
    <updated>20240315T035001Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>inverted follicular keratosis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue revealing well-circumscribed endophytic growth of squamous cells featuring lobular extension into the dermis, with numerous horn cysts. Solar elastosis is also seen. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>old man/head and neck</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Irritated SK [SkiSK]</title>
    <created>20180503T043250Z</created>
    <updated>20260408T022331Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>irritated seborrheic keratosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The epidermis is characterized by a sharply demarcated, exophytic lesion which shows hyperkeratosis and papillomatosis with squamous eddies formation. Chronic inflammatory infiltrate is seen in the dermis.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The epidermis is characterized by a sharply demarcated, enophytic lesion which shows hyperplastic squamous epithelium with several squamous eddies and scattered horn cyst formation. Neutrophilic scale-crust is noted at the surface. Chronic inflammatory infiltrate is seen in the dermis. Immunohistochemically, the Ki67 shows increased nuclear staining confined within basal layer.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>junctional nevus [JCN]</title>
    <created>20190816T081445Z</created>
    <updated>20250425T050754Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Junctional nevus</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows nevus cells in junctional area with a low Ki-67 proliferative index. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Juvenile Xanthogranuloma, JXG</title>
    <created>20180830T070255Z</created>
    <updated>20251208T073306Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="padding-left:40px;">    </div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Juvenile xanthogranuloma.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Microscopic description:</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">The section shows a demarcated, dense dermal infiltrate of foamy histiocytes, with scattered Touton giant cells.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Keloid</title>
    <created>20170831T031527Z</created>
    <updated>20230821T031307Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Keloid</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Section shows </span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">bands of collagen, with fibroblasts and myofibroblasts running in parallel between them in the dermis. </span></span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Keratoacanthoma (KA)</title>
    <created>20170728T062807Z</created>
    <updated>20260315T060710Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>[F]</div><div>ICD code: 1 </div><div>不用Stage</div><div>Last updated: 2026-03-15</div><hr/><div><br/></div><div>Keratoacanthoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The lesion is characterized as a cup-shaped epithelial</div><div>proliferation often with atypical cells, enclosing a central</div><div>keratin-filled plug. The granular cell layer is absent and</div><div>maturation sequence is not altered.</div><div><br/></div><div style="text-align:start;">A. Tumor histological type: Keratoacanthoma </div><div style="text-align:start;">B. Tumor grade: I (well differentiated) </div><div style="text-align:start;">C. Tumor size: ___   cm in maximum dimension.</div><div style="text-align:start;">D. Tumor thickness:  ____ cm.</div><div style="text-align:start;">E. Invasion depth: Invades the dermis </div><div style="text-align:start;">F. Margins of excision:</div><div style="text-align:start;">    1. Peripheral margin: free, _ mm in distance / involved</div><ol start="2"><li><div>Deep margin: free, _ mm in distance / involved</div></li></ol><div>G. Additional tumor features:</div><div>     Lymphovascular Invasion: Absent</div><div>     Perineural Invasion: Absent</div><div>     Necrosis: Absent</div><div>     Mitotic count / 5 hpf (mm2): _______________</div><div>H. Lymph Node: not assessed.</div><div><br/></div><hr/><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20191008T021443Z</created>
    <updated>20191008T021640Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>large cell acanthoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows flat featureless epidermis containing enlarged keratinocytes with hyperpigmentation, which are devoid of atypia. Solar elastosis is seen. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>lipogranuloma.</title>
    <created>20230526T012911Z</created>
    <updated>20230526T013022Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>lipogranuloma</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description: </div><div>Section shows variable-sized spaces in the dermis, surrounded by histiocytes and multinucleated giant cells.</div><div>This is probably due to injection or topical application of oil based substances. Please correlate.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Lobular capillary hemangioma</title>
    <created>20161222T005550Z</created>
    <updated>20231031T063130Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; float: none;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;">Lobular capillary hemangioma</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; float: none;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; float: none;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;">Microscopic description:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; float: none; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;">Section shows a demarcated lesion composed of lobules of capillary channels lined by bland endothelial cells. Mitos    es are occasionally seen. No malignancy is observed.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Lymphoid hyperplasia with eosinophilia</title>
    <created>20180305T051643Z</created>
    <updated>20180305T051741Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Skin, left chest, excision --- Lymphoid hyperplasia with </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">eosinophilia (See Note)</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Note: This case has sent to National Cheng Kung University </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Hospital for diagnosis.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Section shows mixed inflammatory infiltrate composed of </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">abundant eosinophils, lymphocytes and histiocytes in</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">superficial and deep dermis with occasional lymphoid </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">follicle formation.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">No epidermotropism is identified but aggregates of </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Langerhans cells within epidermis are noted.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Immunohistochemically, these lymphocytes are composed a </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">mixed population of cells positive for CD3, CD20 and</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">bcl-2. CD4+ and CD8+ cells show a normal distribution </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">and PD-1 stains only 10-15% of cells with weak staining</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">intensity.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">CD10 immunostain highlights the germinal centers. </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">EBER in situ hybridization is negative.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Note: Eczematous dermatitis is favored.</span></div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Melaning bleaching method</title>
    <created>20161222T012147Z</created>
    <updated>20161222T012219Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>No removal of pigment is noted after melanin bleaching method.</div><div><br/></div><div>Then pigments are removed after melanin bleaching method.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20190821T073524Z</created>
    <updated>20250115T034256Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>mixed tumor (chondroid syringoma).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a well-circumscribed tumor with epithelial strands in a myxoid stroma.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Molluscum contagiosum</title>
    <created>20170728T062820Z</created>
    <updated>20211208T041049Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Molluscum contagiosum.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The section shows an indented dermis as a result of sharply</div><div>delimited and lobulated mass of proliferating epidermis,</div><div>associated with prominent molluscum bodies.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Neurofibroma [NF]</title>
    <created>20180313T051737Z</created>
    <updated>20240920T051824Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>neurofibroma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show a demarcated nodule composed of loosely arranged spindle cells in haphazard arrangement. The lesional cells feature small, wavy or buckled nuclei in a variable collagenous matrix. </div><div><br/></div><div>Degenerative atypia is present.</div><div>By immunohistochemistry, the lesional cells are positive for S100, consistent with the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>neurofibroma with vague plexiform growth [NF]</title>
    <created>20240318T071244Z</created>
    <updated>20250225T052436Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>neurofibroma with vague plexiform growth.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show demarcated nodules composed of loosely arranged spindle cells in vague plexiform growth. The lesional cells feature small, hyperchromatic, wavy or buckled nuclei in a variable myxoid to collagenous matrix.</div><div>By immunohistochemistry, scattered positive cells for S100, EMA and CD34 are seen. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Nevus lipomatosus superficialis</title>
    <created>20170412T062357Z</created>
    <updated>20241202T044722Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>nevus lipomatosus superficialis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>It shows skin tissue with wide spread infiltrate of the dermis by mature adipocytes.</div><div>No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Nevus sebaceus</title>
    <created>20170804T041417Z</created>
    <updated>20240411T030724Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">nevus sebaceus.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Microscopic description:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">The section shows an exophytic lesion revealing papillomatosis and sebaceous gland hyperplasia that open directly into epidermis. It also shows apocrine glands and paucity of hair follicles underneath the lesion. The above-mentioned features are consistent with nevus sebaceus.</span></span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Nevus sebaceus</title>
    <created>20170728T062833Z</created>
    <updated>20260213T050840Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Nevus sebaceus.</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The epidermis exhibits papillomatous hyperplasia with hyperkeratosis. Numerous mature sebaceous glands lie in the</div><div>dermis. The hair structures remain small except for occasional dilated keratin-filled infundibula.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Nevus sebaceus with syringocystadenoma papilliferum, skin, scalp</title>
    <created>20170511T061047Z</created>
    <updated>20240321T054714Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The section shows an exophytic lesion revealing papillomatosis and sebaceous gland hyperplasia that open directly into epidermis. It also shows apocrine glands and</div><div>paucity of hair follicles underneath the lesion. The above-mentioned features are consistent with nevus sebaceus.</div><div><br/></div><div>Syringocystadenoma papilliferum is also present in the background of nevus sebaceus,</div><div>which shows papillary projections with intense lymphoplasmacytic infiltration in the</div><div>stroma. The papillae is covered superficially by squamous epithelium and deeply by</div><div>double-layered epithelium, consisting of inner tall columnar cells and outer cuboidal</div><div>myoepithelila cells. No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20181210T052558Z</created>
    <updated>20181210T053105Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Oak 5雙先不用</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Onychomycosis (nail)</title>
    <created>20170512T063240Z</created>
    <updated>20241120T050844Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;">onychomycosis.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Section shows skin and nail tissue with focal intraepithelial neutrophilic infiltrate. F</span><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">ungal spores and hyphae within the keratin layer are highlighted by PAS.</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210105T050817Z</created>
    <updated>20210105T051119Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>osteoma cutis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show a well-circumscribed nodule of mature lamellar bone focally rimmed by osteoblasts and containing fatty marrow spaces.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20200102T083302Z</created>
    <updated>20260526T032620Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Palisaded granulomatous inflammation. (see description)             </div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows necrobiotic center with peripheral palisading of histiocytes and scattered lymphocytes. No mycobacterial microorganisms are identified by acid fast stain. No fungus is identified by PAS. The histiocytes are highlighted by CD68. Desmin is negative.</div><div><br/></div><div>The differential diagnoses include rheumatoid nodule, granuloma annulare or granulomatous inflammation induced by other causes. Please correlate with clinical features.</div><div><br/></div><div>                         </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20221013T053113Z</created>
    <updated>20221013T053445Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>papillary hidradenoma.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Section shows elongated tubules and papillary strucutures lined by luminal columnar cells with decapitation secretion, and basal cuboidal myoepithelial cells.</div><div>P16 is negative. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20220325T075816Z</created>
    <updated>20241203T062153Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>papillary lesion (see description).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows the squamous epithelium displaying focally and mildly papillary proliferation with hyperkeratotic surface. No obvious koilocytes (perinuclear halo cells) or dysplasia are discerned.</div><div>However, condyloma acuminatum cannot be excluded.</div><div>Please follow-up and correlate clinically.</div><div>No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div>Ancillary studies: deeper-cut.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The specimen consists of a tiny fragment of vulval tissue, in which there is parakeratosis of the squamous epithelium.</div><div>Early papillary structure and equivocal koilocytosis are present but not enough to classify it as condyloma acuminatum. Staining for p16 is focally positive.</div><div>Clinical correlation and follow-up is recommended.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Paronychia</title>
    <created>20180118T030625Z</created>
    <updated>20200618T081719Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div>debridement, removal of partial nail and excision of pyogenic granuloma --- consistent with paronychia.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">It shows laminated keratin indicating nail with focal intraepithelial neutrophilic infiltrate. The overall features are consistent with paronychia.</span></div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div><hr/><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Skin and nail, __ big toe, debridement, removal of partial nail and excision of pyogenic granuloma --- consistent with paronychia.</div><div>                                                        </div><div>Gross description:                                           </div><div>The specimen consists of _ pieces of tissue measuring up to _ cm.</div><div>All for section (decalcification).</div><div><span>    </span><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>It shows laminated keratin indicating nail with focal intraepithelial neutrophilic infiltrate. The overall features are consistent with paronychia.</div><div><br/></div></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Paronychia (with GMS and PAS)</title>
    <created>20170216T085849Z</created>
    <updated>20231031T081004Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/#inbox/15a45db83b8c89e4?compose=15a4625097526a0a</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">Skin and nail, __ big toe, debridement, removal of partial nail and excision of pyogenic granuloma --- consistent with paronychia.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">                                                        </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">Gross description:                                           </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">The specimen consists of _ pieces of tissue measuring up to _ cm.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">All for section (decalcification).</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">It shows laminated keratin indicating nail with focal intraepithelial neutrophilic infiltrate.</span> <span style="font-size: small; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif;">No fungus is identified by PAS. The overall features are consistent with paronychia. <span>    </span></span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Penetrating injury</title>
    <created>20180813T024648Z</created>
    <updated>20250410T042615Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Chronic inflammation, consistent with penetrating injury</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue with epidermial defect and chronic inflammatory infiltrate in the dermis. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pigmented fungus</title>
    <created>20171211T015511Z</created>
    <updated>20250214T042444Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>https://www.google.com.tw/search?q=phaeohyphomycosis&amp;rlz=1C1BEMX_zh-TWTW773TW773&amp;source=lnms&amp;tbm=isch&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjZvZi-gYTYAhXMEbwKHZk4BggQ_AUICigB&amp;biw=1366&amp;bih=662#imgrc=JkjuuFLnXszF2M:</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: 'Open Sans', Arial;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51);">Microscopic description: </span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Open Sans', Arial;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51);">Section shows granulomatous inflammation with large round pigmented fungal forms, which may represent an agent of chromoblastomycosis or phaeohyphomycosis. Correlation with culture is needed for diagnosis.</span></span></span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pilomatricoma</title>
    <created>20170728T063032Z</created>
    <updated>20241231T062135Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:rgb(102, 102, 102);">Pilomatricoma</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The lesion is a pilomatrixoma, composed of nests of benign squamous cells with calcifying ghost cells more evident from the center toward periphery. No evidence of malignancy is seen.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:rgb(102, 102, 102);">Pilomatricoma</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Microscopic description:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Section shows a well demarcated lesion located at deep dermis to superficial subcutis, composed of ghost cells and basaloid cells accompanied by calcification and mixed inflammatory infiltrate as well as occasional multinucleated giant cells. No malignancy is observed.</span></span></div><div>    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20211125T071657Z</created>
    <updated>20241218T063745Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Pilonidal sinus</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows hair shaft fragment in the dermis associated with foreign body reaction and mixed inflammatory infiltrate. Sinus lined by squamous epithelium is seen.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>porokeratosis.</title>
    <created>20231201T092643Z</created>
    <updated>20231201T092708Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>cornoid lamella formation, suggestive of porokeratosis. </div><div>see NOTE.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows keratin-filled epidermal invagination with cornoid lamella. Dyskeratosis is seen. Chronic inflammatory cell infiltrate is seen in the dermis. </div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: These findings may be suggestive of porokeratosis.</div><div>However, cornoid lamella formation may also occur as a non-specific finding in a variety of conditions. Clinical correlation is mandatory for the diagnosis.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210308T051632Z</created>
    <updated>20210308T051652Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Proliferating epidermal cyst.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The cyst is lined by stratified squamous epithelium connecting to the overlying skin. Its lumen contains keratin material. Focal epithelial proliferation with horn cysts and squamous eddies formation is seen. No evidence of inflammation or malignancy is noted.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20200410T061050Z</created>
    <updated>20230822T023305Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Proliferating trichilemmal tumor (PTT). See Note.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show a well-circumscribed solid and cystic dermal</div><div>tumor focally connecting to the overlying skin. It is composed of squamous epithelium with prominent</div><div>infolding and containing homogeneous eosinophilic keratin.</div><div>The neoplastic cells are monomorphous without significant</div><div>cytological atypia. Extending to subcutaneous fat is also</div><div>seen. Focal and limited irregular outlines and growth are seen, which is present adjacent to inflammatory and forein body reaction, and is in favor of reactive rather than malignant change. The surgical margin is free, with closest distance of 2 mm from deep margin.</div><div><br/></div><div>Note: Most cases of PTT have shown benign biological</div><div>behavior. In rare instances, malignant transformation may</div><div>occur. Follow-up is suggested.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div><div><br/></div><div>Ref. S0902598</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Proliferative actinic keratosis</title>
    <created>20161201T234327Z</created>
    <updated>20161201T234335Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows dysplastic squamous epithelium focally exhibiting proliferating in budlike down growths into the papillary dermis. The dermis underlying the keratosis shows solar elastosis and vascular ectasia.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pyogenic granuloma</title>
    <created>20170728T062855Z</created>
    <updated>20260302T063822Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Pyogenic granuloma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue revealing surface ulceration and mixed inflammatory infiltrate in the underlying stroma, accompanied by vascular proliferation organized in lobular arrangement.</div><div>No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210422T095241Z</created>
    <updated>20210422T095619Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Reticulohistiocytosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a dermal nodule composed of histiocytoid cells revealing ground glass cytoplasm, vesicular nuclei, and prominent nucleoli, and including multinucleated forms.</div><div>An admixure of lymphocytes and occasional eosinophils is seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>By immunohistochemistry, the lesional cells are positive for CD68 but not S100 or SMA, consistent with the diagnosis.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180625T054346Z</created>
    <updated>20180625T054350Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>rom</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20221101T031501Z</created>
    <updated>20240122T015814Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>sebaceoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows dermal nodule consisting of basaloid cells and</div><div>mature sebocytes. MLH1 and MSH2 show intact nuclear</div><div>expression.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>sebaceous adenoma (please see description).</title>
    <created>20190301T094619Z</created>
    <updated>20231204T073737Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>sebaceous adenoma (please see description).<br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows lobules of mature sebaceous cells with a</div><div>minority of basaloid germinative cells at the periphery.</div><div><br/></div><div>Stainings for MLH1 and MSH2 show intact nuclear</div><div>expression. However, most of the tumor cells show no MSH6 expression.</div><div><br/></div><div>Sebaceous adenoma forms part of the spectrum of the Muir-Torre syndrome. Please correlate clinically.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Sebaceous hyperplasia</title>
    <created>20170308T044543Z</created>
    <updated>20260108T023955Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Sebaceous hyperplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows enlarged sebaceous lobules surrounded by a single layer of germinative cells, connecting into dilated folliculosebaceous ducts.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170308T070340Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T055617Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Section shows a subcutaneous lesion composed of proliferation of fibroblasts and myofibroblasts admixed with some lymphocytes, suggesting fibrosis after a prior infection/inflammation. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;">The skin tissue shows mild acanthosis with multinodular dermal proliferation of fibroblasts and myofibroblasts admixed with some lymphocytes in the underlying dermis.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170308T044624Z</created>
    <updated>20170308T044635Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Section shows well-demarcated tumor composed of lobules of mature sebaceous cells with a minority of basaloid germinative cells at the periphery. The surface is ulcerative.</span><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">No malignancy is observed.</span></span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170627T075136Z</created>
    <updated>20170627T075149Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Sections show the epidermis with full-thickness replacement by neoplastic squamous cells that show hyperchromatism, enlargement and loss of polarity of nuclei without stromal invasion.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Severely atypical compound melanocytic lesion 建議excision</title>
    <created>20211015T023547Z</created>
    <updated>20230616T030836Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Severely atypical compound melanocytic lesion, cannot excludde/bordering on early melanoma. Complete excision is recommended. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SKI15 [with gross]</title>
