  <note>
    <title>SKI15FB Epidermal inclusion cyst, inflamed.</title>
    <created>20200605T063604Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T030405Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Epidermoid cyst, inflamed.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The dermally-located cyst is lined by squamous epithelium with keratin fragments in its lumen, associated with a foreign body granulomatous response. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SKI15IN Epidermal inclusion cyst, inflamed.</title>
    <created>20180507T050849Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T030433Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Epidermoid cyst, inflamed.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The dermally-located cyst is lined by squamous epithelium with keratin fragments in its lumen. Inflammatory reaction is seen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SKI16</title>
    <created>20170728T062726Z</created>
    <updated>20240423T081631Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Epidermoid cyst, ruptured and inflamed.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The dermally-located cyst shows partial destruction of its lining squamous epithelium. At its epithelial-stromal interface, there is marked mixed inflammatory cell infiltration that includes foreign body type <span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">multinucleated giant cells. The lumen is partially obliterated by deposition of similar type of inflammatory cells, with identifiable residual keratin material.                            </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SKI16 C/W</title>
    <created>20180417T045239Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T054715Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with epidermoid cyst, ruptured and inflamed.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows skin tissue featuring marked mixed inflammatory cell infiltration that includes foreign body type multinucleated giant cells. There is identifiable residual keratin material. The overall features are consistent with epidermal inclusion cyst, ruptured and inflamed.        </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SKI16ABSCESS Epidermal inclusion cyst, ruptured and inflamed, with focal abscess formation</title>
    <created>20180112T060743Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T030548Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Epidermal inclusion cyst, ruptured and inflamed, with focal abscess formation</span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">The dermally-located cyst shows partial destruction of its </span>lining squamous epithelium. There is marked mixed inflammatory cell infiltrate that includes foreign body type multinucleated giant cells, with focal abscess formation. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Skin</title>
    <created>20150130T035239Z</created>
    <updated>20180530T022548Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Calcinosis cutis</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows skin tissue with dermal and subcutaneous deposition of numerous calcified materials. It may be a cutaneous phenomenon secondary to local tissue</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">degeneration ("dystrophy") or may occur when the final metabolic defects give rise to elevated serum calcium or phosphate. Clinical correlation is suggested.</span></div></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Dermatofibroma</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows skin tissue with acanthosis of epidermis and a dermal proliferation of bland-looking spindle cells featuring oval or spindle nuclei admixed with some foamy histiocytes. Tumor extension to the subcutis is noted. No cellular atypia or increased mitotic activity is observed. Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are negative for CD34, excluding dermatofibrosarcoma protuberans. No frank malignancy is observed.</span></div></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Hidrocystoma</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">It shows skin tissue with a dermally-located cystic lesion lined by inner columnar</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">cells and outer myoepithelial cells. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br/></div></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br/></div></div><div><br/></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Squamous epithelial proliferative lesion (建議total excision)</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">It shows hyperkeratic and acanthotic squamous epithelium with mild cellular atypia and focally dyskeratosis. No adequate stromal tissue is present for evaluation of invasiveness. Underlying malignancy cannot be excluded. Total excision may be necessary for precise diagnosis.</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Irritated serrheic keratosis</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows hyperkeratosis and papillomatosis of squamous epithelium with proliferation of variably pigmented basal cells and presence of horn cysts. Marked subepithelial chronic inflammatory infiltrate is noted.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Necrosis and suppurative inflammation</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows skin tissue with ulceration accompanied by extensive necrosis admixed with dense PMNs infiltration in the underlying dermis and superficial subcutis. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><br/></div></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><br/></div><div><br/></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></div><ul><li><br clear="none" /></li></ul><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Congo red</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Staining for Congo red shows apple-green birefringence under polarized light. </span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br clear="none" /></div></div><div><br/></div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Skin tag (eyelid)</title>
    <created>20181203T130934Z</created>
    <updated>20241209T032505Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>fibroepithelial polyp (skin tag)</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows acanthotic epithelium with hyperkeratosis, papillary projections with inner fibrovascular core lined by stratified squamous epithelium. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Skin tag (Fibroepithelial polyp)</title>
    <created>20170728T062938Z</created>
    <updated>20230526T043830Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">fibroepithelial polyp (skin tag).</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The polypoid skin tissue is lined by an intact stratified squamous epithelium and its stroma is made up of loose collagen.      <span>    </span>  </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Skin tags and intradermal nevus IDN</title>
    <created>20170803T060254Z</created>
    <updated>20240221T033006Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>skin tags and intradermal nevus.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows small polypoid lesions lined by an intact stratified squamous epithelium</div><div>and supported by fibrous connective tissue stroma. There is also one small intra-</div><div>dermal nevus, featuring an intact epidermis with intradermal depositions of lobules or</div><div>nests of mature nevus cells. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><span>    </span><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SKISK  Seborrheic keratosis, adenoid type</title>
    <created>20180106T003212Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T055610Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>seborrheic keratosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows thin proliferating strands of basaloid cells arising from the epidermis. These cells are pigmented. Pseudohorn cysts formation is also seen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SKISK Seborrheic keratosis</title>
    <created>20170609T062936Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T055616Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/eyeeyelidseborrheickeratosis.html</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>seborrheic keratosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The epidermis is characterized by a sharply demarcated, exophytic lesion which exhibits <span style="font-size: 10pt;">a<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">canthosis </span></span>with hyperkeratosis and several horn cysts formation.</div><div>                        </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SKISK Seborrheic keratosis</title>
    <created>20170728T062903Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T055603Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Seborrheic keratosis</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimen is composed of     piece(s) of        tissue,</div><div>measuring</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are submitted in one cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The epidermis is characterized by a sharply demarcated, exophytic lesion which</div><div>exhibits hyperplasia of variably pigmented basaloid cells with exuberant keratin</div><div>production (hyperkeratosis) and several horn cyst formation.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SKISK+FUNGUS</title>
    <created>20190304T044234Z</created>
    <updated>20250919T030823Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Seborrheic keratosis with fungal infection.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The epidermis is characterized by a sharply demarcated, exophytic lesion which exhibits hyperplasia of variably pigmented basaloid cells with exuberant keratin production (hyperkeratosis) and several horn cyst formation. Some fungal spores are seen within the superficial keratin layer.    </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210430T092001Z</created>
    <updated>20230116T043958Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Spitz nevus.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows nests of large epithelioid cells with abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm and prominent nucleoli, extending from the epidermis into the reticular dermis in a wedge-shaped configuration. The Ki-67 index is low (2%). The lesional cells are positive for melan-A, consistent with the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color: rgb(252, 18, 51);">Ki67, HMB-45, P16, Cyclin D1</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180301T042356Z</created>
    <updated>20230731T045822Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">steatocystoma.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Section shows cystic lesion with serpiginous wall lined by thin squamous epithelium. Sebaceous glands are seen adjacent to or contiguous with cyst wall.    </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210812T045209Z</created>
    <updated>20210812T045228Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>storiform collagenoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a well-circumscribed dermal nodule composed of hypocellular hyalinized collagen bundles separated by clefts and arranged in a storiform pattern. Bland-looking spindle-shaped cells are seen. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Scattered multinucleated giant cells are seen.</div><div>giant cell collagenoma. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Suggestive of Chromoblastomycosis.</title>
    <created>20250214T043249Z</created>
    <updated>20250706T080027Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Suggestive of Chromoblastomycosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic Description:</div><div>The section shows skin tissue revealing pseudoepitheliomatous hyperplasia, mixed inflammatory</div><div>infiltrate, including multinucleated giant cells, along with abscess formation in the dermis. There are large, round,</div><div>pigmented fungal forms, which may represent an agent of chromoblastomycosis. Correlation with culture is needed for</div><div>diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Ancillary Studies:</div><div>PAS: Fungi highlighted.</div><div>AE1/AE3: Pseudoepitheliomatous hyperplasia without</div><div>malignancy.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>suggestive of Herpes simplex / zoster infection.</title>
    <created>20210119T092254Z</created>
    <updated>20210119T092539Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>suggestive of Herpes simplex / zoster infection.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows intraepidermal blisters associated with intracellular edema. Several epithelial cells reveals nuclear changes of nuclear moulding, chromatin margination and multinucleation. Involvement of folliculosebaceous unit is seen. Focal epidermal necrosis is seen.</div><div>The features are suggestive of Herpes simplex / zoster infection. Please correlate.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>suppurative granulomatous inflammation with fungal infection.</title>
    <created>20181113T060741Z</created>
    <updated>20200211T082557Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>suppurative granulomatous inflammation with fungal infection.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue with dermal granulomatous inflammation with central collections of necrotic debris and neutrophils, surrounded by multinucleated giant cells, histiocytes and lymphoplasmacytic infiltration. Some fungal hyphae and yeast form are identified by PAS. No mycobacterial microorganisms are identified by acid fast stain.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Suppurative inflammation with fungal infection [Supp2]</title>
    <created>20180619T084633Z</created>
    <updated>20241121T024958Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Suppurative inflammation with fungal infection</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows suppurative inflammation with collections of neutrophils, liquified debris of necrotic cells and edema fluid.   Fungal spores and hyphae are identified within necrotic keratin layer. </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Syringocystadenoma papilliferum</title>
    <created>20250509T014613Z</created>
    <updated>20250509T014811Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Syringocystadenoma papilliferum.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The section shows cystic invaginations with papillae lined by a double-layered epithelium, composed of inner tall columnar cells and outer cuboidal cells.</div><div>The stroma exhibits mononuclear inflammatory infiltrate.</div><div>No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Syringoma</title>
    <created>20180503T014703Z</created>
    <updated>20180503T015134Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows a syringoma, which is composed of clusters of small ducts lined by two cells thick epithelium with comma-shaped extensions in a fibrotic stroma.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Thrombosed vessel</title>
    <created>20170627T074740Z</created>
    <updated>20250305T073342Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">thrombosed vessel (capillary aneurysm).</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The slide shows a single greatly dilated vessel that lacks a</div><div>discernible wall or is surrounded by a delicate fibrous layer.</div><div>The lumen contains a partially organized thrombus.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">thrombosed vessel (capillary aneurysm).</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows a single greatly dilated vessel with its lumen containing a partially organized thrombus.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>traumatic neuroma.</title>
    <created>20200813T023520Z</created>
    <updated>20260212T081026Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Traumatic neuroma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows irregular haphazardly arranged proliferation of regenerating nerve fascicles of various sizes and shaped embeddded in a fibrous stroma.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>trichilemmal cyst (pilar cyst)</title>
    <created>20181205T095057Z</created>
    <updated>20250319T030350Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>trichilemmal cyst (pilar cyst)</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows an intradermal cyst lined by squamous epithelium containing homogeneous eosinophilic keratin.</div><div>Focal forein body giant cell reaction and cholesterol crystals are seen.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>There is focal epithelial infolding into the cyst lumen, but is not enough to classify it as proliferating trichilemmal cyst/tumor. There is no cellular atypia nor invasive growth. However, follow-up of the lesion is still recommanded.</div><div><br/></div><div>The margin is free of tumor (__ mm in distance).</div><div>        </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Trichilemmoma</title>
    <created>20170227T025100Z</created>
    <updated>20231114T083201Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Trichilemmoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows proliferation of uniform cells with peripheral palisading and focal  thickened eosinophilic basement membrane as demonstrated by PAS.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180921T025958Z</created>
    <updated>20180921T030014Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Trichoadenoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show numerous keratocysts lined by stratified squamous epithelium which manifests epidermoid keratinization in the dermis. Some of the cysts rupture with inflammatory reaction.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Trichoblastoma</title>
    <created>20181005T053216Z</created>
    <updated>20181005T053227Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Trichoblastoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a dermal nodule composed of lobules of</div><div>basaloid cells with conspicuous peripheral palisading in a</div><div>dense fibrous stroma. Keratocyst formation, stromal mucin</div><div>deposition are focally seen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Trichoepithelioma</title>
    <created>20161208T090455Z</created>
    <updated>20250828T044729Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Trichoepithelioma.</div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The section shows dermal nodule composed of keratocysts and sheets of basaloid cells, featuring </div><div>peripheral palisading, in fibrous stroma. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>trichofolliculoma.</title>
    <created>20200721T055643Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T030333Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>trichofolliculoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a cystic cavity lined by stratified squamous epithelium containing keratinous debris and hair shaft fragments. Arising from its wall are numerous hair follicles. Stromal granulomatous inflammation are present.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20190703T045003Z</created>
    <updated>20250508T052916Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Tumoral calcinosis</div><div><br/></div><div>calcinosis cutis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>It shows multiple spaces lined by epithelioid and giant cells. The spaces contain eosinophilic debris undergoing calcification. The overall features are most consistent with tumoral calcinosis.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>ulceration.</title>
    <created>20200820T030734Z</created>
    <updated>20200820T031052Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>ulceration.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue with ulceration and infiltrate of acute inflammatory cells admixed with necrotic debris.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Verruca plantaris</title>
    <created>20170728T063047Z</created>
    <updated>20241212T032757Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>https://www.google.com.tw/search?q=pulmoplantar+wart&amp;rlz=1C1BEMX_zh-TWTW773TW773&amp;oq=pulmoplantar+wart&amp;aqs=chrome..69i57j0l5.6879j0j4&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>verruca plantaris.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The skin tissue shows parakeratosis and acanthosis with conspicuous intracytoplasmic eosinophilic inclusions. </div><div>No malignancy is observed.</div><div><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><hr/><div>palmoplantar wart.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The skin tissue shows parakeratosis and acanthosis with conspicuous intracytoplasmic eosinophilic inclusions. </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 10pt;">No malignancy is observed.</span>   </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Verrucoid and endophytic squamous proliferations</title>
    <created>20241002T015846Z</created>
    <updated>20241002T020032Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>verrucoid and endophytic squamous proliferations.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows verrucoid and endophytic squamous proliferations with hyperkeratotic surface.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>a/w fungal, leishmanial, and non-tuberculous mycobacterial infection</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Verrucous cyst.</title>
    <created>20241219T031705Z</created>
    <updated>20241219T031808Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><br/></div><div>The section shows a cystic lesion lined by squamous epithelium with hypergranulosis and papillomatosis.</div><div>Focal pale cell changes are noted.</div><div>Hyperkeratosis and parakeratosis are present on the surface.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Verrucous lesion (c/w VV 但拿到太表淺)</title>
    <created>20170117T062940Z</created>
    <updated>20230711T024526Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: gotham;">Verrucous lesion </span></span><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: gotham;">(please see description)</span></div><div style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: gotham;"><br/></span></div><div style="font-size: 14px;"></div><div style="font-size: 14px;"></div><div style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: gotham;">Microscopic description:</span></span></div><div style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">Section shows a superficial sampling of the lesion which features marked hyperkeratosis and hyperplastic squamous epithelium with verrucous projections. The</span> <span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">features can be consistent with verruca vulgaris. However, the base of the lesion is not discerned in this specimen. Please correlate clinically.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>VV</title>
    <created>20171211T055216Z</created>
    <updated>20230921T040841Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">verruca vulgaris.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">The epidermis shows acanthosis, hyperkeratosis and papillomatosis with koilocytes in the superficial spinous layer. There is cupping effect of the rete ridges. The dermis shows chronic inflammatory reaction. No malignancy is observed.        </span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">verruca vulgaris.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The epidermis shows acanthosis with alternating para- and hyperkeratosis and papillomatosis with koilocytes in the superficial spinous layer.</div><div>No malignancy is observed.        </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>VV + FUNGUS</title>
    <created>20230921T040837Z</created>
    <updated>20230921T040855Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>-- verruca vulgaris.</div><div>-- fungal infection.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The epidermis shows acanthosis, hyperkeratosis and papillomatosis with koilocytes in the superficial spinous layer. There is cupping effect of the rete ridges. The dermis shows chronic inflammatory reaction. </div><div>Some fungal spores are seen within the superficial keratin layer.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Warty dyskeratoma.</title>
    <created>20210920T093026Z</created>
    <updated>20210920T093048Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Warty dyskeratoma.                                             </div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a well-circumscribed cup-shaped lesion composed of a proliferation of keratinocytes, with prominent acantholysis, with suprabasal clefting, dyskeratosis, corps ronds, corps grains, and an overlying parakeratotic plug. Mitoses are common.The surrounding stroma contains chronic inflammatory cell infiltrate.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Xanthelasma</title>
    <created>20170728T063125Z</created>
    <updated>20220908T031432Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Skin, ___ eyelid, excision --- xanthelasma.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimen is composed of one piece of skin tissue, measuring ____ cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>All are embedded in one cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows collection of formy histiocytes in the dermis. No evidence of malignancy</div><div>is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>有綁線的Skin/SCC</title>
    <created>20150723T090224Z</created>
    <updated>20251203T091356Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source-url>file:///F:\2018%20修改版-給癌症中心\皮膚癌_SCC.doc</source-url>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Squamous cell carcinoma.</div><div>    </div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimen consists of one fragment of skin, measuring _ x _ x _ cm with two _long strands indicating the 12 o'clock and two _short strands indicating the 6 o'clock.</div><div>A ___tumor is seen, measuring _ x _ x _ cm.</div><div>It measures _ cm to 12 o'clock, _ cm to 3 o'clock, _ cm to 6 o'clock and _ to 9 o'clock surgical margins, respectively.</div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>          </div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Tumor histological type: Squamous cell carcinoma</div><div>Tumor grade: II (moderately differentiated)</div><div>Tumor size: _ cm in maximum dimension.</div><div>Tumor thickness: _ cm.</div><div>Invasion depth: Invades the dermis / subcutis</div><div>Margins of excision:</div><div>  Peripheral margin: Uninvolved by tumor, _ cm in distance. Involved by tumor.</div><div>  Deep margin: involved by tumor</div><div>Additional tumor features:</div><div>  Lymphovascular Invasion: Absent</div><div>  Perineural Invasion: Absent</div><div>  Necrosis: Absent</div><div>  Mitotic count / 5 hpf (mm2): __</div><div>Lymph Node: Not assessed.</div><div>Additional finding:</div><div>  Solar elastosis.</div><div>  Hemorrhage and suppurative inflammation are seen.</div><div>Immunohistochemical stain:</div><div>  p40: positive.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>                              </div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 10pt;">適用</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica-Bold;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">cutaneous carcinoma (CC),</span></span> <span style="font-family: Helvetica-Bold;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="color:#f14f9a;">basal cell carcinoma (BCC)</span></span></span> <span style="font-family: Helvetica-Bold;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">of head and neck </span></span></div><en-media style="--en-naturalWidth:400; --en-naturalHeight:483;" hash="1ace75cc883dda51be4aa305229a0ddf" type="image/png" /><div><b><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#0433ff;">cutaneous carcinoma (CC), basal cell carcinoma (BCC)</span></span></span></b></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#bc0058;">*Deep invasion</span></span></span> <span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#010101;">is defined as invasion beyond the subcutaneous fat</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#010101;">or>6 mm (as from the granular layer of adjacent normal epidermis</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#010101;">to the base ofthe tumor); perineural invasion for T3 classification</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#010101;">is as tumor cells within the nerve sheath of a nerve lying</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#010101;">deeper than the dermis or measuring >=0.1 mm in caliber,</span></span></span> <span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#010101;">or presenting</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#010101;">with clinical or radiographic involvement of named nerves without skull</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:#010101;">base invasion or transgression.</span></span></span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
